  <a href="https://adobe.sharepoint.com/:p:/r/sites/CampaignManagedSvcEngineering/Shared%20Documents/PPC/Ketchup%20H1%202025%20PPC.pptx">Ketchup H1 2025 PPC.pptx</a>
</h1>
<h1 data-nh-numbering="7. " style="text-align: left;">Summary:</h1>
<ul>
  <li>Ketchup is an AI-Powered CSO Summarization Tool for Slack designed to reduce Time to Catch Up.</li>
  <li>It translates lengthy Slack CSO Warrooms into concise, easy-to-understand summaries.</li>
  <li>Built on Docker containers running on EC2 with FastAPI, powered by Azure OpenAI (GPT-4).</li>
</ul>
<h1 data-nh-numbering="8. ">STATUS: CA Approved 28-01-25 | PPC Approved 27-02-25</h1>
<h1 data-nh-numbering="9. ">Instructions:</h1>
<ol>
  <li>You must be authorized to run Ketchup. To check your access or request it, run: <strong>/ketchup access</strong>
  </li>
  <li>Add the Ketchup app to any Slack warroom in the CSO workspace by typing <strong>@Ketchup</strong> and pressing enter. Accept the prompt to add it to the channel.</li>
  <li>Type <strong>/ketchup status</strong> in the chat to get a concise summary with current status, actions taken by engineers, timeline and next steps.</li>
  <li>Type <strong>/ketchup report</strong> to get a detailed incident report with impact analysis, actions taken, evidence and RCA.</li>
  <li>Type <strong>/ketchup query &lt;question&gt;</strong> inside a war room to ask Ketchup questions in natural language for specific details.</li>
  <li>Type <strong>/ketchup list</strong> to get a list of active war rooms that Ketchup is a member of.</li>
  <li>Access the <strong>Ketchup Home Tab</strong> by clicking on the Ketchup app in your Slack sidebar and selecting "Home" at the top. Here you can:<ul>
      <li>See a personalized greeting (e.g., "Hi YourName!").</li>
      <li>Customize your preferences for summaries (product focus, detail level, time window).</li>
      <li>Access the "Support &amp; Feedback" section to find the <a href="https://wiki.corp.adobe.com/display/neolane/Ketchup+How-To">Ketchup How-To Guide</a>, join the <a href="https://adobe.enterprise.slack.com/archives/C08CQN1JCSC">#ketchup-feedback</a> channel, and submit feedback.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>
