<h1 data-nh-numbering="13. ">Production Services (8 Total):</h1>
<p>
  <strong>Services on Both prod1 &amp; prod2 (HA):</strong>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>nginx - Reverse proxy with least_conn load balancing</li>
  <li>ketchup-app (2 replicas/server) - FastAPI webhook receiver</li>
  <li>mcp-jira - Node.js JIRA integration service</li>
  <li>ketchup-access-monitor - Health monitoring service</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <strong>Singleton Services (prod1 only):</strong>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>ketchup-status-updater - Hourly status automation</li>
  <li>jira-reporter - JIRA report generation</li>
  <li>channel-metadata-updater - Metadata extraction</li>
  <li>ketchup-maintenance-fetcher - Maintenance detection</li>
</ul>
<h1 data-nh-numbering="14. ">Feature Flags (Environment-Based):</h1>
<p>
  <strong>Source of Truth:</strong> infrastructure/docker-compose.yml</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <code>USE_PIPELINE_PROCESSING=true</code> - 59% performance improvement</li>
  <li>
    <code>KETCHUP_USE_HTTPX=true</code> - HTTP/2 support, 5-8% gain</li>
  <li>
    <code>KETCHUP_HTTP2_ENABLED=true</code> - HTTP/2 multiplexing</li>
  <li>
    <code>KETCHUP_KEEPALIVE_ENABLED=true</code> - Connection pooling</li>
  <li>
    <code>KETCHUP_STRUCTURED_JSON_OUTPUT=true</code> - 10-20% faster AI responses</li>
  <li>
    <code>KETCHUP_STATUS_UPDATER_FEATURE=true</code> - Hourly status automation</li>
  <li>
    <code>KETCHUP_JIRA_REPORTER_FEATURE=true</code> - JIRA report generation</li>
  <li>
    <code>KETCHUP_MAINTENANCE_DETECTION=true</code> - Maintenance alerts</li>
</ul>
<h1 data-nh-numbering="15. ">DynamoDB Schema:</h1>
<p>
  <strong>TTL Configuration (Important for Restore State):</strong>
</p>
<pre>TimeToLiveStatus: ENABLED
AttributeName: temp_unarchive_expiry

Purpose: When a channel is temporarily unarchived, the bot marks this with a TTL 
set to 180 seconds. This ensures temporary state is automatically cleaned up after TTL expires.</pre>
<h1 data-nh-numbering="16. ">Logging Architecture (Updated):</h1>
<p>
  <strong>Local Docker json-file Driver:</strong>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Max size: 10MB per file</li>
  <li>Max files: 3 per service (30MB total)</li>
  <li>Storage: /opt/ketchup/logs/</li>
  <li>No CloudWatch (local only)</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <strong>Custom Log Viewer:</strong>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Real-time streaming via SSE</li>
  <li>Okta 2FA authentication</li>
  <li>Monitor up to 9 containers simultaneously</li>
  <li>Advanced search, regex, saved searches</li>
</ul>
<h1 data-nh-numbering="17. ">Deployment:</h1>
<p>
  <strong>Current Version:</strong> v2.360.346</p>
<p>
  <strong>Method:</strong> Shell script (infrastructure/deploy-ketchup.sh)</p>
<ul>
  <li>Auto-increments version (v2.X.X.X format)</li>
  <li>Builds Docker images, pushes to ECR</li>
  <li>Zero-downtime rollout (prod1 first, then prod2)</li>
  <li>Excludes singletons from prod2 deployment</li>
  <li>Rollback supported</li>
</ul>
<h1 data-nh-numbering="18. ">Performance Optimizations (Oct 2025):</h1>
<p>
  <strong>Phase 1 - Pipeline Processing:</strong> 4 concurrent workers, 200-300% improvement<br/>
  <strong>Phase 2 - HTTP/2 &amp; Keep-Alive:</strong> 94.7% connection reuse, 7-11% additional gain<br/>
  <strong>Combined:</strong> 300-400% overall performance improvement</p>
